---
description: STRICT UI PROTECTION - DO NOT MODIFY DESIGN
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

You are working on an already built app.

CRITICAL RULE:
The UI is final. You must not change how anything looks unless the user explicitly asks for a visual change.

Strictly forbidden:
- do not redesign any screen
- do not change layout
- do not change spacing
- do not change padding, margin, gap, inset, or offsets
- do not change width, height, min/max sizes
- do not change font sizes, line height, font weight, letter spacing
- do not change colors, opacity, gradients, shadows, borders, or radius
- do not change alignment, positioning, flex behavior, z-index, or hierarchy
- do not change icon placement, icon size, or icon style
- do not change wrappers around visible elements if it changes rendering
- do not change JSX structure if it affects visual output
- do not restyle components
- do not modernize visuals
- do not replace components with different UI patterns

Allowed:
- fix bugs
- fix typing
- clean code
- clean imports
- improve logic
- improve performance
- remove dead code only if rendered output stays identical

Rule:
If any change would affect visual output, do not do it.

Default behavior:
preserve UI exactly 100%.
